I'll calculate the requested financial ratios step by step using the data from the financial statements.

## Current Ratio
Current Ratio = Total Current Assets / Total Current Liabilities
Current Ratio = $23,990,150.22 / $4,319,436.82 = 5.55

## Quick Ratio
Quick Ratio = (Current Assets - Inventory) / Current Liabilities
Quick Ratio = ($23,990,150.22 - $5,600,000.00) / $4,319,436.82 = $18,390,150.22 / $4,319,436.82 = 4.26

## Debt to Asset Ratio
Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets
Debt to Asset Ratio = $4,319,436.82 / $33,610,271.98 = 0.13

## Debt to Equity Ratio
Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity
Debt to Equity Ratio = $4,319,436.82 / $29,290,835.16 = 0.15

## Cash Flow to Debt Ratio
Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities / Total Liabilities
Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = (-$6,316,405.44) / $4,319,436.82 = -1.46
